1 tive endocrinology services;
2 (c) A plan to provide equitable access to assisted reproductive technology for all residents
3 of this state;
4 (d) The feasibility of obtaining federal financial participation in or securing other federal
5 resources to support the plan described in paragraph (c) of this subsection; and
6 (e) Legislative changes necessary to implement the recommendations under this sub-
7 section.
8 SECTION 4. ORS 743B.005 is amended to read:
9 743B.005. For purposes of ORS 743.004, 743.007, 743.022, 743.416, 743.417, 743.535, 743A.101,
10 743B.003 to 743B.127, 743B.109, 743B.128, 743B.250 and 743B.323 and section 2 of this 2026 Act:
11 (1) “Actuarial certification” means a written statement by a member of the American Academy
12 of Actuaries or other individual acceptable to the Director of the Department of Consumer and
13 Business Services that a carrier is in compliance with the provisions of ORS 743B.012 based upon
14 the person’s examination, including a review of the appropriate records and of the actuarial as-
15 sumptions and methods used by the carrier in establishing premium rates for small employer health
16 benefit plans.
17 (2) “Affiliate” of, or person “affiliated” with, a specified person means any carrier who, directly
18 or indirectly through one or more intermediaries, controls or is controlled by or is under common
19 control with a specified person. For purposes of this definition, “control” has the meaning given that
20 term in ORS 732.548.
21 (3) “Affiliation period” means, under the terms of a group health benefit plan issued by a health
22 care service contractor, a period:
23 (a) That is applied uniformly and without regard to any health status related factors to an
24 enrollee or late enrollee;
25 (b) That must expire before any coverage becomes effective under the plan for the enrollee or
26 late enrollee;
27 (c) During which no premium shall be charged to the enrollee or late enrollee; and
28 (d) That begins on the enrollee’s or late enrollee’s first date of eligibility for coverage and runs
29 concurrently with any eligibility waiting period under the plan.
30 (4) “Bona fide association” means an association that:
31 (a) Has been in active existence for at least five years;
32 (b) Has been formed and maintained in good faith for purposes other than obtaining insurance;
33 (c) Does not condition membership in the association on any factor relating to the health status
34 of an individual or the individual’s dependent or employee;
35 (d) Makes health insurance coverage that is offered through the association available to all
36 members of the association regardless of the health status of the member or individuals who are
37 eligible for coverage through the member;
38 (e) Does not make health insurance coverage that is offered through the association available
39 other than in connection with a member of the association;
40 (f) Has a constitution and bylaws; and
41 (g) Is not owned or controlled by a carrier, producer or affiliate of a carrier or producer.
42 (5) “Carrier” means any person who provides health benefit plans in this state, including:
43 (a) A licensed insurance company;
44 (b) A health care service contractor;
45 (c) A health maintenance organization;
