23 (18) “Initial enrollment period” means a period of at least 30 days following commencement of
24 the first eligibility period for an individual.
25 (19) “Late enrollee” means an individual who enrolls in a group health benefit plan subsequent
26 to the initial enrollment period during which the individual was eligible for coverage but declined
27 to enroll. However, an eligible individual shall not be considered a late enrollee if:
28 (a) The individual qualifies for a special enrollment period in accordance with 42 U.S.C. 300gg
